Sort Characters in a String | Sort the characters of a string in ascending order. |

import java.util.*;
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String str = "Banana";
        System.out.println("sort characters in a string: "+ sortChar(str));
    }
    public static String sortChar(String str){
        
        char[] arr = str.toCharArray();
        
        Arrays.sort(arr);
        
        return new String(arr);
        
    }
}

output:
sort characters in a string: Baaann
